 barehanded and combo cards, which allow the player to combine two weapons to create a better weapon. All of this is wrapped around a time system, as the game takes place over 72 ingame hours. Both story and side missions must be completed during a certain time frame, or they'll be gone forever. Particularly damning when losing story missions, as it may require you to go back to a saved game (On that note, SAVE OFTEN, and use multiple slots).\n\nSo, as a wrap up:\nPROS:\n[list]\n    [*] Decent playtime (My first playthrough lasted about 24 hours, with some sandbox mode gameplay)\n    [*] Controls well (With a controller)\n    [*] A fun gameplay loop of saving survivors, defeating psychopaths, and tending to the plot\n    [*] A B-movie tone with all the cheesiness and one-liners you could ask for\n[/list]\n\nNEUTRALS:\n[list]\n    [*] Timed story and side missions (I personally enjoyed it for its uniqueness)\n    [*] Possible lack of variety (The side objectives tend to be samey, with some standouts. The gameplay can also become repetetive if you don't embrace the combo weapon system)\n    [*] Challenging (I could definitely see people finding the game too hard, especially if going into some areas unprepared. On a side note, psychopaths can have frustrating attack patterns that take a while to learn and overcome)\n[/list]\n\nCONS:\n[list]\n    [*] Occasional game crashes, particularly during cutscenes. I've only had the game crash twice, but have seen others report near constant crashing, so proceed with caution in that regard.\n    [*] Sandbox mode is a bit lacking, especially if you're not interested in completing the challenges\n[/list]"}, {"votes_down": 1, "written_during_early_access": false, "voted_up": true, "language": "english", "timestamp_created": 1500741813, "weighted_vote_score": "0.507822", "steam_purchase": true, "votes_funny": 0, "recommendationid": "33724876", "votes_up": 7, "comment_count": 0, "author": {"steamid": "76561197996040992", "num_reviews"