Mode, which is an alternate gamemode that does away with both the missions and the timelimit, and just lets you roam around the map killing zombies, psychopaths, and doing fairly enjoyable challenges. If you just want to screw around and kill zombies, this is what you've wanted. It's also a nifty feature for those who don't like replaying Dead Rising games over and over in order to get better at the game and eventually get the best ending, as you can level up to 50, get combo cards and so on without the time pressure getting to you.\n\nNow, a general summary of the game rather than simply what OTR includes. Dead Rising can be difficult to describe, but it's a 3rd person beat-em up (for lack of a term I'm more familiar with) where you plough through hordes of zombies. A large gimmick of the series if your ability to pick up anything that isn't nailed down in order to use it as a weapon (I'm still being surprised by how many random items there are I've never seen before, or seeing new moves I didn't know certain weapons had), and Dead Rising 2 introduced the ability to combine weapons into significantly stronger Combo Weapons.\n\nSo, the core gameplay of Dead Rising is effectively buttonmashing into hordes, and finding better stuff with which to buttonmash into hordes. This is where Dead Rising puts twists on the gameplay to make it consistently enjoyable, rather than making it Dead Rising 4.\n\nFor one thing, durability is a thing. Weapons in Dead Rising are NOT things you can just keep around. A combo weapon might get you through 60 zombies if it's an especially durable one. Taking out a crowd of zombies will take several weapons' worth of durability. You need to figure out if it's worth burning your combo weapons, or if you can scavenge enough mediocre weapons from your immediate environment to deal with the zombies fine.\n\nSecondly, Psychopaths. Psychopaths require preperation, careful management and skilful gameplay in order to get past them. It's not Dark Souls or anything, but a single Psychopath is far more of a threat than any amount of zombies, and many of them are used in pretty clever ways- For example, during a certain period of time, three snipers set up in the centre of the map. You could invest time in clearing them out, or side-step them on the map, and it's the player's choice to figure out which approach they'd rather take as well as which approach they think will consume the least time.\n\nAnd speaking of time, yes, Dead Rising's stories have a time limit. This isn't just something the game implemented to be a dick, it's to add degrees of strategy to... Basically everything. Farming PP (exp, basically) will cost time. Getting money will cost time. The more time you consume, the closer you get to having negative consequences- Sidequests each have individual time limits, critical story missions have time limits and you will fail the main quest if you aren't on time for one, and Frank himself needs to consume Zombrex every 24 hours or he'll succumb to his infection. If you're going for 100% completion, this results in an extremely strategic and really awesome balancing act. I was turned off from the series when I heard about the time limit, but after playing it, the time limit really isn't an issue. Don't let it stress you out and see it as another objective- \"Okay, I need to be here within 20 minutes, but that's 20 minutes of time to do whatever I want in the meantime... Hey, who wants to raid a zombie-infested casino?!\" (or, if you're being pragmatic, you'd be picking up magazines you want for your build. But nobody plays Dead Rising to be pragmatic)\n\nI can absolutely, highly recommend this game. IMO it's the overall best Dead Rising game. The original still has a lot of value, and if you JUST want to fuck around and kill zombies without caring about the series' other elements Dead Rising 3 is arguably superior, but DR2 executes a lot well as a sequel, and Off The Record improved its problems.\n\n[spoiler]but seriously if you take one thing away from this review, it's that you should NOT buy dead rising 4[/spoiler]"}, {"votes_down": 2, "written_during_early_access": false, "voted_up": true, "language": "english", "timestamp_created": 1501640614, "weighted_vote_score": "0.498012", "steam_purchase": true, "votes_funny": 0, "recommendationid": "33962043", "votes_up": 4, "comment_count": 0, "author": {"steamid": "76561198011134507", "num_reviews": 11, "last_played": 1501798858, "num_games_owned": 188, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_forever": 1124}, "timestamp_updated": 1501640614, "received_for_free": false, "review": "controller didnt get detected so i had to fix it, otherwise its my favorite dead rising. fucking awesome gameplay and you play as frank. buy this shit"}, {"votes_down": 1, "written_during_early_access": false, "voted_up": false, "language": "english", "timestamp_created": 1500963910, "weighted_vote_score": "0.500391", "steam_purchase": true, "votes_funny": 0, "recommendationid": "33780618", "votes_up": 1, "comment_count": 0, "author": {"steamid": "76561198062948220", "num_reviews": 4, "last_played": 1503368027, "num_games_owned": 93, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_forever": 300}, "timestamp_updated": 1500963944, "received_for_free": false, "review": "I got This game on Speical during the steam winter sale.\nit is a good game itself used to love playing it on xbox 360 the reason I downvoted it has nothing to do with the gameplay its the bugs this game has and how poorly its been ported over to pc\n\nI managed to play 5 hours but thats all I'm going to be able to play because now it crashes everytime I try to start it up and Yup I tried too fix what problems it might of had but still wont work \n\nso if your willing too push your luck and be able to play it past the 5 hour mark and risk no refund go for it otherwise dont take the risk"}, {"votes_down": 3, "written_during_early_access": false, "voted_up": true, "language": "english", "times